    "text": "Regarding ADD-PATH ID vs RD for preserving multiple paths:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/>RD makes it easy to preserve multiple paths through the pinch point, while also making it easy to identify the source.<br/>ADD-PATH can do the former, but complicates the latter.<br/>If RD does open up scaling challenges, it can be made the same in all the PE’s (just as ADD-PATH can be disabled).<br/>IOW, using RD provides the choice of easy source identification (which one can opt out of, should scaling become a problem), but ADD-PATH doesn’t offer that choice. Am I understanding it correctly?<br/>"
